{{Infobox person | name = Ali Wakrim | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Birth-date and age|birth date†}} for living people supply only the year unless the exact date is already widely published, as per WP:DOB --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date†|birth date†}} --> | death_place = | nationality = [[Morocco|Moroccan]] | other_names = | occupation = Businessman | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = | net worth =$1 billion dollars }} '''Ali Wakrim''' is a Moroccan businessman. He and his family share ownership in the [[Akwan Group|Akwa Group]] with [[Aziz Akhannouch]] and his family. The two men's fathers partnered to form the company, along with [[Afriqua Gaz]], which Wakrim chairs along with [[Maghreb Oxygene]].<ref>https://www.forbes.com/profile/ali-wakrim/?list=africa-billionaires Forbes profile</ref>
Billionaires tycoon Ali Wakrim and his family share ownership in Akwa Group with Moroccan billionaire Aziz Akhannouch. Wakrim's late father Ahmed partnered with Aziz Akhannouch's father to form Afriquia Gaz in 1959. Wakrim is chairman of the liquid petroleum gas distributor, which reported $400 million in revenues in 2014. He is also vice president of Akwa Group, the holding company for Afriquia Gaz and for Maghreb Oxygene, a chemical manufacturer.his net worth is estimated to be 1 billion dollars <ref>{{cite web |title=Ali Wakrim & family |url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/ali-wakrim/#20f85764385c |website=Forbes |accessdate=16 August 2018}}</ref>
