{{Infobox person | image = | image_size = | name = Andrew Firestone | imagesize = 200px | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1975|7|10}} | birth_place = [[Santa Barbara, California]], [[United States|U.S.]] | birth_name = Andrew Boulton Firestone | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Businessman | spouse = [[Ivana Bozilovic]] {{nowrap|<small>(2008-present)</small>}} | children = 3 | relations = }}
'''Andrew Boulton Firestone''' (born July 10, 1975) is an American TV reality show personality. He is the son of [[Brooks Firestone]], a grandson of [[Leonard Firestone]], and a great-grandson of [[Firestone Tire and Rubber Company]] founder [[Harvey Firestone]] and [[Idabelle Smith Firestone|Idabelle Smith]].{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}
==Early life== Educated at [[Stevenson School]] and [[Westminster School (Connecticut)|Westminster School]], he graduated from the [[University of San Diego]] in [[business administration]] where he also was a member of the football team, in 1998.
==Career== Professional Career Andrew Firestone is Principal and Founder of StonePark Capital, a Santa Barbara-based hospitality firm that focuses on the acquisition and development of select service hotels, and applies a disciplined set of strategies which prioritizes investor return. Currently StonePark capital has projects in Santa Barbara, Morgan Hill, Santa Rosa, and San Luis Obispo CA.
===The Bachelor=== Firestone was the third [[bachelor]] on the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] reality series ''[[The Bachelor (US TV series)|The Bachelor]]''. On the show, premiered in March 2003, Firestone courted 25 bachelorettes, progressively eliminating them, and eventually selected one of the group for a continuing relationship. Andrew selected and proposed to [[The Bachelorette|Jen Schefft]], who accepted and moved to California to be with him. The couple decided to go their separate ways in December 2003, but remained friends.
===Other television appearances=== In 2005, Firestone participated in the fifth [[Celebrity Poker Showdown]] tournament on [[Bravo (US TV channel)|Bravo]]. He won his first-round game, but placed third in the tournament championship. Firestone played for the charity [[Direct Relief]].
In 2006, Firestone appeared in an episode of [[VH1]]'s ''[[Celebrity Paranormal Project]]''.
Firestone is the host of a lifestyles series entitled ''Billionaires Car Club'', distributed by [[American Television Distribution]]. It first aired in May 2008.
Firestone also made an appearance on episode two of ''[[Flavor of Love Girls: Charm School]]'' on VH1.
Firestone and his wife have appeared in television advertisements for the Baby Bullet.
==Personal life== On July 5, 2008,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/Bachelor-Andrew-Firestone-Marries-Ivana+ |title=EXCLUSIVE: Bachelor Andrew Firestone Marries Ivana |accessdate=2009-01-06 |date=2008-07-05 |publisher=''[[Us Weekly]]'' |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080822155840/http://www.usmagazine.com/Bachelor-Andrew-Firestone-Marries-Ivana%2B |archivedate=2008-08-22 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> Firestone married actress/model [[Ivana Bozilovic]] at St. Mark's in the Valley Episcopal Church in [[Los Olivos, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.instyleweddings.com/weddings/gallery/1,,20219557,00.html |title=Andrew Firestone and Ivana Bozilovic |accessdate=2009-01-06 |publisher=''[[In Style]]'' |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125043804/http://www.instyleweddings.com/weddings/gallery/1%2C%2C20219557%2C00.html |archivedate=25 January 2009 |deadurl=no }}</ref> Firestone and Bozilovic have three children: sons Adam Brooks (born March 21, 2009)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20267190,00.html |title=Andrew Firestone and Wife Welcome a Baby Boy |date=2009-03-21 |accessdate=2009-03-21 |publisher=''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090325061638/http://www.people.com/people/article/0%2C%2C20267190%2C00.html |archivedate=25 March 2009 |deadurl=no }}</ref> and Shane (born January 27, 2014),<ref>http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/andrew-firestones-wife-ivana-gives-birth-to-third-child-baby-boy-shane-2014271</ref> and daughter Anja Jasmine (born April 15, 2011).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2011/04/15/bachelorandrew-firestone-welcomes-daughter-anja-jasmine/|title=Bachelor Andrew Firestone Welcomes Daughter Anja Jasmine|date=2011-04-15|accessdate=2011-04-15|publisher=''[[People (magazine)|People]]''}}</ref>
