{{Infobox book | name = Business/IT Fusion | title_orig = | translator = | image = Cover Business-IT Fusion.JPG | caption = First edition cover | author = Peter Hinssen | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Belgium]] | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject = | genre = | publisher = MachMedia | pub_date = 2009 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]]) | pages = 276 pp | isbn = 978-90-813242-3-6 | oclc= 431959785 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Business/IT Fusion: How to Move Beyond Alignment and Transform IT in Your Organization''''' is a business book by [[Peter Hinssen]], published in 2009. It discusses an approach to [[IT management]] different to the classic model of [[business/IT alignment]]. In place of alignment focused on the collaboration between business and IT, Hinssen suggests that the future evolution in IT lies in the convergence of the two parties: integrating IT into the business rather than treating it as a supplier. The work is presented as a guidebook to "IT 2.0".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.computerweekly.com/feature/Can-the-IT-department-survive-Web-20|title=Can the IT department survive Web 2.0?|accessdate=November 24, 2013|work=[[Computer Weekly]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digimedia.be/News/nl/5060/column-sant-in-eigen-land.html|title=Column: sant in eigen land|date=December 22, 2008|accessdate=November 24, 2013|work=Digimedia|first=Ben|last=Caudron|language=Dutch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.informationweek.com/team-building-and-staffing/global-cio-business-it-alignment-is-dead----whats-next/d/d-id/1076281?|title=Global CIO: Business/IT Alignment 'Is Dead' -- What's Next?|date=February 4, 2009|accessdate=November 24, 2013|work=[[InformationWeek]]|first=Bob|last=Evans}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.6minutes.be/Artikel.aspx?ArtikelID=14735&RubriekID=19|title=Peter Hinssen: fusion business–IT en livre|date=April 27, 2009|accessdate=November 24, 2013|work=6minutes|language=French}}</ref>
