{{distinguish|Dara Ó Briain}}
'''Daire O'Brien''' is an Irish broadcaster and journalist. He is best known for being the presenter and anchorman of [[RTÉ Sport]]'s coverage of the [[Pro14]] rugby union competition,<ref name="rte">{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/tv/eleventhhour/talk-to-us.html|title=RTÉ Eleventh Hour - Talk To Us|publisher=RTÉ Sport|accessdate=21 December 2013}}</ref> and has been with RTÉ since 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/sport/rugby/rabo-direct-pro-12/2010/0830/269942-magners/|title=RTÉ launches Magners League Coverage|work=RTÉ Sport|date=30 August 2010|accessdate=21 December 2013}}</ref> Before this he presented for [[Setanta Sports]], where he was one of their most recognisable faces. Here he was successful until Setanta Sports went bankrupt in 2010, after which he moved to RTE Sport and began broadcasting for them.<ref>{{cite news|first=Melanie|last=Finn|url=http://www.herald.ie/entertainment/tv-radio/rte-poaches-obrien-to-lead-the-magners-pack-2314203.html|title=RTÉ poaches O'Brien to lead the Magners pack|newspaper=[[Evening Herald]]|date=27 August 2010|accessdate=27 August 2010}}</ref> He has also contributed to [[Newstalk]]. He has written for the ''[[Irish Independent]]'', ''[[The Sunday Times]]'', ''[[The Sunday Business Post]]'' and the ''[[Sunday Tribune]]'' and reported for ''[[Prime Time (Irish TV programme)|Prime Time]]'' in the 1990s.<ref name="rte"/> He narrated the RTÉ series ''Tidiest of Towns'' in 2007.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iftn.ie/news/?act1=record&only=1&aid=73&rid=4280834&tpl=archnews&force=1|title='Tidiest of Towns' to kick off on RTÉ|work=ITFN|date=20 November 2007}}</ref>
His family home is Carrigrohane Castle in Cork, his father Leo was a businessman and his older brother is the well-known socialite businessman [[Breifne O'Brien]], who was recently found guilty of defrauding a number of people, some of whom were longtime friends, of sums totaling more than €10m<ref name=bet_con>{{cite news|url=http://www.sundayworld.com/columnists/index.php?aid=7922 |title=RTÉ star's €3k bet 'con': TV pundit Daire refused to pay wager says bookie girl |newspaper=[[Sunday World]] }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Louise |last=Hogan |url=http://www.independent.ie/national-news/courts/celtic-tiger-party-boy-breifne-obrien-bailed-out-by-pensioner-mum-3235719.html |title=Celtic Tiger party boy Breifne O'Brien bailed out by pensioner mum |newspaper=Irish Independent |date=21 September 2012 |accessdate=21 September 2012 |quote=Mr O'Brien comes from an affluent family in Cork, where his father Leo was a successful businessman. His younger brother Daire O'Brien is a familiar face to many as an RTÉ rugby presenter. Their family home, Carrigrohane Castle, overlooks the River Lee. }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
