'''Odd Gleditsch Jr.''' (born 16 May 1929) is a Norwegian businessperson.
He was born in [[Sandefjord]] as a son of [[Odd Gleditsch Sr.]]<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Odd, Gleditsch Jr.|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Odd%2C_jr._Gleditsch|language=Norwegian|accessdate=7 July 2009}}</ref> He was a second cousin once removed of [[Rolf Juell Gleditsch|Rolf]], [[Ellen Gleditsch|Ellen]], [[Kristian Gleditsch|Kristian]] and [[Henry Gleditsch]].<ref name=snl2>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Gleditsch|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Gleditsch|language=Norwegian|accessdate=7 July 2009}}</ref>
He took his [[chemical engineering]] education in the United States. He was hired in his father's company [[Jotun (company)|Jotun Odd Gleditsch]] in 1953. He became CEO in 1967 and saw through a merger to form the company [[Jotun (company)|Jotun]] where he was CEO from 1972 to 1979. He was also chairman of the board from 1972 to 2000.<ref name=snl/>
